## 3. CORE COMPONENT LIBRARY (`components/hub/*`)

These components must be built as lean, reusable units.

### The Ascension Indicators
*   `LevelBadge.tsx`: A visual indicator of the user's current status (`Reviewer` [L1], `Pilot` [L2], `Protocol Engineer` [L3]).
*   `XPBar.tsx`: A gamified progress bar showing claims cleared, rules written, and bounties claimed to unlock the next tier.

### The Learning & Trust Components
*   `AITrustScoreCard.tsx`: A daily metric showing the AI's first-pass accuracy rate. Builds psychological trust.
*   `GlassBoxAlert.tsx`: A reusable alert banner that explains *why* the AI flagged a claim (e.g., "Medicare NCD 150.3 conflict detected"). No black boxes.
*   `DualPaneReviewer.tsx`: A split-screen layout component used for both training and live review. Left side = Source EHR note. Right side = AI Staged 837 Claim.

### The Protocol Engineering Components (Level 2/3)
*   `LogicGateBuilder.tsx`: A visual, no-code rule builder. Allows billers to construct `IF [Payer] AND [Condition] THEN [Action]` rules without writing SQL or JSON.
*   `RuleImpactSimulator.tsx`: Before saving a rule, this component runs it against the last 30 days of claims to show the "Predicted Impact" (e.g., "This rule would have flagged 42 claims").

### The Bounty Network Components
*   `BountyBoard.tsx`: A Kanban-style or list-view board showing available overflow batches. Includes filters for Payer, Specialty, and Complexity.
*   `BountyCard.tsx`: A single Bounty listing. Must display: Batch Size (e.g., 50 Claims), Reward ($150), and Expiry Time.
*   `BountyWallet.tsx`: A financial dashboard component showing earned bounties, pending payouts, and historical earnings.

